# Exchange Design System — Mandatory Prototype Rules

## Figma Sources (always reference first)
- **XDS Exchange Design System:** https://www.figma.com/design/S5vzHnfEkTU1uETKnVOl7x/XDS---Exchange-Design-System
- **Exchange Brand Playbook:** https://www.figma.com/slides/Oyb9M17fbUWZl4C7ZTO3jQ/Exchange-Brand-Playbook

These tokens are extracted directly from the Figma file via REST API (last synced 2026-03-24).

---

## Rule 1 — Always import the design system
Every new prototype HTML file MUST import both CSS files at the top:

```html
<link rel="stylesheet" href="./design-system/tokens.css">
<link rel="stylesheet" href="./design-system/components.css">
```

Adjust paths if in a subdirectory (e.g. `../design-system/`).

---

## Rule 2 — Use design tokens for ALL visual properties
Never hardcode colours, spacing, font sizes, radii, or shadows. Use `var(--xds-*)`:

```css
/* ✅ Correct */
background: var(--xds-bg-widgets);
color: var(--xds-text-primary);
padding: var(--xds-space-12);
border-radius: var(--xds-radius-lg);
border: 1px solid var(--xds-border);

/* ❌ Never do this */
background: #141416;
color: white;
padding: 24px;
```

---

## Rule 3 — Dark theme by default
ALL Exchange prototypes use the dark theme. The page root must always be:

```css
body {
  background: var(--xds-bg-primary);   /* #09090A — Slate/950 */
  color: var(--xds-text-primary);      /* #FFFFFF */
}
```

---

