## Rule 5 — Use semantic dark-theme tokens in layouts

```css
/* Surfaces */
--xds-bg-primary       /* #09090A  page */
--xds-bg-widgets       /* #141416  cards/panels */
--xds-bg-muted         /* #1B1B1F  subtle */
--xds-bg-secondary     /* #28292E  secondary */
--xds-bg-tooltip       /* #464853  tooltips */

/* Text */
--xds-text-primary     /* #FFFFFF */
--xds-text-secondary   /* #9597A8 */
--xds-text-muted       /* #7B7D8E */
--xds-text-accent      /* #92D1FF  blue highlight */
--xds-text-success     /* #00DC82 */
--xds-text-destructive /* #FE4A6B */
--xds-text-warning     /* #F7B721 */

/* Borders */
--xds-border           /* #28292E  default */
--xds-border-input     /* #5D606F  inputs */
--xds-ring             /* #B1B2BF  focus rings */
```

---

## Rule 6 — Typography
Always use `'Inter Variable'` (with `'Inter'` as fallback). Apply via `var(--xds-font-family)`.

Named type styles (use `font: var(--xds-type-X)` shorthand):
- Headings: `--xds-type-heading1` (32px/52px), `--xds-type-heading2` (24px/40px), `--xds-type-heading3` (18px/28px)
- Body: `--xds-type-body1` (14px/20px w:400), `--xds-type-body2` (12px/16px w:400)
- Labels: `--xds-type-label1` (14px/20px w:500), `--xds-type-label2` (12px/16px w:500)
- Links: `--xds-type-link1`, `--xds-type-link2` — same size as labels but use `--xds-text-accent` colour

---

## Rule 7 — Component classes
Use `.xds-*` classes for all standard UI components before writing custom CSS:

- Buttons: `.xds-btn .xds-btn-primary` / `.xds-btn-secondary` / `.xds-btn-ghost` / `.xds-btn-danger`
- Cards: `.xds-card`
- Inputs: `.xds-input`, `.xds-select`, `.xds-textarea`
- Status badges: `.xds-badge .xds-badge-active` / `.xds-badge-scheduled` / `.xds-badge-draft` / `.xds-badge-ended` / `.xds-badge-deactivated`
- Tables: `.xds-table`, `.xds-table-wrap`
- Tabs: `.xds-tabs`, `.xds-tab`
- Navigation: `.xds-nav`
- Info blocks: `.xds-info-block` (add `.success`, `.warning`, `.error`, `.purple` modifiers)
- Modals: `.xds-modal-overlay`, `.xds-modal`

---

## Rule 8 — Campaign status badges
Always use XDS badge classes for campaign lifecycle states:
- Draft → `.xds-badge .xds-badge-draft`
- Scheduled → `.xds-badge .xds-badge-scheduled`
- Active → `.xds-badge .xds-badge-active`
- Ended → `.xds-badge .xds-badge-ended`
- Deactivated → `.xds-badge .xds-badge-deactivated`

---

## Rule 9 — Spacing
Use the spacing scale exclusively — no arbitrary pixel values:

`--xds-space-2` (4px) → `--xds-space-4` (8px) → `--xds-space-6` (12px) →
`--xds-space-8` (16px) → `--xds-space-12` (24px) → `--xds-space-16` (32px)

---

## Rule 10 — When the design system doesn't cover something
Check the Figma XDS file first. Build new components using existing tokens only.
Never introduce new colour values, sizes, or spacing values outside the token scale.
